The lowest order approximation is obtained by the approximation νh ≈ λ0ϵ and Γh,h′ ≈ νhδh,h′, yielding
var [ J r , r ′ eff ] var [ J ] = 1 + ( λ 0 ϵ ) 2 N hid var [ J ] = 1 + ( λ 0 J 0 ϵ ) 2 ( 1 - f ) 1 ( p N ) 2 a - 1 . (7)
This result varies linearly with f, while numerical evaluation of the variance shows obvious curvature for f ≪ 1 and J0 ≲ 1, so we need to go to higher order. This becomes tedious very quickly, so we will only work to O ( ϵ 4 ) (it turns out O ( ϵ 3 ) corrections vanish).
